comments.body:
@mheon With this we're closer, but not quite there.  This PR doesn't affect the requirement for a *base-image* to build off of.  Rather it automates the process of translating base-images into cache-images. 
Most importantly, the new cache-images will also have the libpod integration tests run against them (in the PR).  They can also be used with the `hack/get_ci_vm.sh` script for even more in-depth playing/debugging/testing.

(I will add a card for the work required to bring in a new F30 base-image.)
